<http://www.spektrix.com/earlymusicvancouver/event/10201AJHJGJMTBHDNGMTSMTVVGPNSHHLL>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "A Little Night Music with Mozart ";
  schema:description """
	<h1>A Little Night Music with Mozart</h1><span><br/></span><img src=\"https://system.spektrix.com/earlymusicvancouver/files/5b2234ed-bfa9-4515-a41c-4e259ae96275.jpg\" /><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>W.A. Mozart’s KV 525, Eine Kleine Nachtmusik, is arguably one of the most recognizable pieces in the history of classical music. But it is only one of countless “Serenatas” or serenades  –  pieces written for entertainment in the evening hours. We pair Mozart’s classic tune, freshly performed on period instruments, with a lesser-known piece from his earlier life in Salzburg: The Serenata Notturna, KV 239. This eclectic programme also includes a fanciful quintet by Boccherini about 18th century night-life in Madrid, instrumental songs by Dowland and Purcell, and an intriguing night-watch tune by Austrian composer Heinrich Ignaz Franz Biber, in which even the audience will participate.
""";
  schema:startDate "2026-10-17T19:30:00"^^xsd:dateTime;
  schema:image <https://system.spektrix.com/earlymusicvancouver/files/5b2234ed-bfa9-4515-a41c-4e259ae96275.jpg>;
  schema:location <https://spektrix.com/earlymusicvancouver/location/401ANPJQJQPQMRSBDNMVNLSPGTRBVQVRH>;
  schema:organizer <https://spektrix.com/earlymusicvancouver/organization/early-music-vancouver>;
  schema:url <https://www.earlymusic.bc.ca/events/a-little-night-music-with-mozart/>;
  schema:offers _:78f1e3f00e524974ab72909aa5a3a4a92983;
  schema:duration "PT60M";
  schema:endDate "2026-10-17T20:30:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

_:78f1e3f00e524974ab72909aa5a3a4a92983 a schema:AggregateOffer;
  schema:lowPrice "15.0";
  schema:priceCurrency "CAD" .

<http://www.spektrix.com/earlymusicvancouver/event/10601APSKMRRDLKDGKBKNPNLTDRGCSHLR>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Amanda Forsythe & Opera Prima - Tormento Seicento ";
  schema:description """
	<h1>Amanda Forsythe & Opera Prima -Tormento Seicento</h1><span><br/></span><img src=\"https://system.spektrix.com/earlymusicvancouver/files/5fd9691f-023c-4108-8fdd-71f081bf6bb0.jpg\" /><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>“ In many ways, the music of the early Baroque period bears a stronger relationship to jazz improvisation than to the late Baroque composers,”writes soprano Amanda Forsythe in her program notes. “ Musicians of the early Baroque were masters of improvisation and they invented melodies and harmonies with skill and confidence. The goal of this period in music was expression — the singer was at an advantage, with the text and melody notated, but the heart of this operation was the Basso Continuo, the musicians that interpreted the figured bass line. ”
""";
  schema:startDate "2027-01-22T19:30:00"^^xsd:dateTime;
  schema:image <https://system.spektrix.com/earlymusicvancouver/files/5fd9691f-023c-4108-8fdd-71f081bf6bb0.jpg>;
  schema:location <https://spektrix.com/earlymusicvancouver/location/401ANPJQJQPQMRSBDNMVNLSPGTRBVQVRH>;
  schema:organizer <https://spektrix.com/earlymusicvancouver/organization/early-music-vancouver>;
  schema:url <https://www.earlymusic.bc.ca/events/amanda-forsythe-opera-prima-tormento-seicento/>;
  schema:offers _:78f1e3f00e524974ab72909aa5a3a4a92984;
  schema:duration "PT60M";
  schema:endDate "2027-01-22T20:30:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

