<http://www.spektrix.com/earlymusicvancouver/event/8201APNKPTCPSVLMMRDKJCTKBHRDCGHGR>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Amanda Forsythe sings Handel";
  schema:description """
	<h1>Amanda Forsythe sings Handel</h1><span><br/></span><img src=\"https://system.spektrix.com/earlymusicvancouver/files/f067423f-90fc-4fbc-8dd7-3da24c744d3e.jpg\" /><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>This exceptional concert features the return of internationally-acclaimed soprano Amanda Forsythe with the Pacific Baroque Orchestra under the direction of Alexander Weimann. The performance features Handel arias originally written for Elisabeth Duparc (‘La Francesina’) and includes the world premiere of Métis composer Pat Carrabré’s “The Mother Tree” based on Suzanne Simard’s novel “Finding The Mother Tree”.
""";
  schema:startDate "2025-09-27T19:30:00"^^xsd:dateTime;
