<http://www.spektrix.com/earlymusicvancouver/event/11401ADJMJHLSTCBJCSJGTJRVLDRSDLQV>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Bach Dances";
  schema:description """
	<h1>Bach Dances</h1><span><br/></span><img src=\"https://system.spektrix.com/earlymusicvancouver/files/fbb3d6ef-fc45-40fd-b5a0-edda792e1e06.jpg\" /><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Bach Dances is a world premiere contemporary dance production conceived by award-winning choreographer and opera stage director Idan Cohen. A co-production between Ne.Sans Opera and Dance, The Dance Centre and Early Music Vancouver, the work reimagines Bach’s first three cello suites as a powerful theatrical experience of live music and contemporary dance. The suites will be performed live by celebrated cellist Elinor Frey, and feature exceptional dancers, evocative costumes, and striking visual imagery.
""";
