<http://www.spektrix.com/earlymusicvancouver/event/12001ALNGHTPHGCKCMSTDNQBDRDVTJPQB>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Bach with Weimann: The Compass Rose";
  schema:description """
	<h1>Bach with Weimann: The Compass Rose</h1><span><br/></span><img src=\"https://system.spektrix.com/earlymusicvancouver/files/3266d3a8-aa31-4d2d-984a-8c551db6a168.jpg\" /><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>While we know and love Bach for his cantatas, oratorios, concertos, and chamber music, he never seems more himself than on the organ. His writings for the ‘king of all instruments’ (W.A. Mozart) open the gates to an entire universe of harmony and polyphony, achieving a degree of freedom impossible for any other instrument, and allowing for a unique window into Bach’s mind
""";
  schema:startDate "2026-08-01T15:00:00"^^xsd:dateTime;
