<http://www.spektrix.com/earlymusicvancouver/event/9803APJMBSPQJQHHVQDHJQRGNBVQQNLSJ>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Die schöne Müllerin - Franz Schubert";
  schema:description """
	<h1>Die schöne Müllerin - Franz Schubert</h1><span><br/></span><img src=\"https://system.spektrix.com/earlymusicvancouver/files/7cb4d419-84a2-4d7d-9423-38af0fa25aba.jpg\" /><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Music contains all the power of the unsaid; it guides our understanding of the text but also our deepest feelings while following it. Franz Schubert shows a masterful use of this power in his song cycle Die schöne Müllerin: The twenty songs trace a journey through love and loss: A wandering miller falls in love with a miller’s daughter but is displaced by a rival hunter. Heartbroken and obsessed with his own death, he imagines the flowers sprouting from his grave and ultimately drowns himself; the water lulling him to his final rest. Yet, within this tragic tale, are some of Schubert’s most beguiling melodies.
""";
  schema:startDate "2026-08-05T19:30:00"^^xsd:dateTime;
  schema:image <https://system.spektrix.com/earlymusicvancouver/files/7cb4d419-84a2-4d7d-9423-38af0fa25aba.jpg>;
  schema:location <https://spektrix.com/earlymusicvancouver/location/401ANPJQJQPQMRSBDNMVNLSPGTRBVQVRH>;
  schema:organizer <https://spektrix.com/earlymusicvancouver/organization/early-music-vancouver>;
  schema:url <https://www.earlymusic.bc.ca/events/die-schone-mullerin-franz-schubert/>;
  schema:offers _:78f1e3f00e524974ab72909aa5a3a4a92995;
  schema:duration "PT60M";
  schema:endDate "2026-08-05T20:30:00"^^xsd:dateTime .

