  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Schubert & Boccherini: Mimosa String Quintet";
  schema:description """
	<h1>Schubert & Boccherini: Mimosa String Quintet</h1><span><br/></span><img src=\"https://system.spektrix.com/earlymusicvancouver/files/fff53dbb-131d-4b96-b107-dfbf7f6b26ab.jpg\" /><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Franz Schubert’s final chamber work, the String Quintet in C major is often described as having “bottomless pathos” and regarded as one of the greatest chamber music compositions. Boccherini’s mastery of string writing shines in his elegant and dramatic Quintetto Op. 29 No. 6 in G Minor. His Fandango is a vibrant, rhythmically intense work infused with Spanish flair.	
""";
