  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Songline: Musical Hike";
  schema:description """
	<h1>Songline: Musical Hike</h1><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><img src=\"https://system.spektrix.com/earlymusicvancouver/files/5d17d9f9-d3b4-4286-8b35-18dda234cf29.jpg\" /><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Songline: Musical Hike, is a unique and intimate opportunity to experience both the inherent music of nature, and the ways in which nature transforms and enriches music. Participants join Artist-in-Residence Marc Mauillon as he sings selections from his album for solo voice, Songline. Audience members journey together through the forest, pausing at intervals to experience the expressive power of the unaccompanied voice among the trees.
