  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Strawberry Fields";
  schema:description """
	<h1>Strawberry Fields</h1><span><br/></span><img src=\"https://system.spektrix.com/earlymusicvancouver/files/413398e3-8f14-426f-a25e-9c7c7e8f2689.jpeg\" /><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Strawberry Fields is a joyous feast of rustic dances from the 18th century. Featuring Ruckus’ dazzling arrangements of Ignatius Sancho’s 12 Country Dances for the year 1779 and the evergreen trio sonatas of George Frederic Handel, this program will have audiences craving to get on their feet.	
